title: Jalan Bahar Clay Studios: Guan Huat Dragon Kiln
blurb: Explore traditional dragon kiln and artist community.
description: Discover the art of pottery at Jalan Bahar Clay Studios, home to the Guan Huat Dragon Kiln. This unique space showcases traditional pottery-making techniques and the works of local artists. Explore the kiln, learn about the history of clay art, and appreciate the craftsmanship of the resident artists. It's an enriching experience for families interested in art and culture, offering a glimpse into Singapore's heritage and the creative process behind ceramic art. The studio provides a hands-on experience, allowing visitors to engage with the art form and understand the intricacies of working with clay. A visit to Jalan Bahar Clay Studios is an educational and inspiring outing for all ages.

title: Jalan Bahar Clay Studios: Dragon Kiln & Community
blurb: Explore a traditional dragon kiln and artist community.
description: Discover the Jalan Bahar Clay Studios, home to the Guan Huat Dragon Kiln, one of the last surviving wood-fired kilns in Singapore. Witness traditional pottery techniques and explore the artist community. Learn about the history of ceramics in Singapore and the importance of preserving this cultural heritage. The studios offer a unique glimpse into the world of pottery and the dedication of the artists who keep this craft alive. Visitors can observe the firing process (when available) and appreciate the artistry involved in creating ceramic pieces. The dragon kiln represents a significant part of Singapore's industrial past and continues to be a working studio for local potters. It's a great place to learn about the history of pottery in Singapore.
